HEADWORD: Buckthorn
<hw>Buck"thorn`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A genus (<spn>Rhamnus</spn>) of shrubs or trees. The shorter
branches of some species terminate in long spines or thorns. See
<er>Rhamnus</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sea buckthorn</b></col>, <cd>a plant of the genus
<gen>Hippopha⟦eum⟧</gen>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bucktooth</ent>⟦br⟧
